PLO chief Yasser Arafat has been treated twice for  exhaustion in the past week, spending the night in a hospital here on Monday,  Palestinian colleagues said Thursday.
Tunisian and Palestinian doctors advised Arafat to rest after a medical  examination last Friday but after suffering a relapse Monday he was admitted  to the military hospital in Tunis where he underwent more tests, they said.
But he has since returned to work full-time at Palestine Liberation  Liberation headquarters in Tunis, they said.
